Field Documentation

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::dsa_en

Enable DSA parsing.

This field should not be set for DPI ports. 0 = Any DSA header is ignored. 1 = DSA is parsed.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::fulc_en

Enable Fulcrum tag parsing.

0 = Any Fulcrum header is ignored. 1 = Fulcrum header is parsed.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::hg2_en

Enable HiGig 2 parsing.

This field should not be set for DPI ports. 0 = Any HiGig2 header is ignored. 1 = HiGig2 is parsed. PKI_GBL_PEN[HG_PEN] must be set.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::hg_en

Enable HiGig parsing.

This field should not be set for DPI ports. 0 = Any HiGig header is ignored. 1 = HiGig is parsed. PKI_GBL_PEN[HG_PEN] must be set. At most one of FULC_EN, DSA_EN or HG_EN may be set.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::inst_hdr

INST header.

When set, the eight-byte INST_HDR is present on all packets (except incoming packets on the DPI ports).

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::lg_custom

Layer G Custom Match Enable.

0 = Disable custom LG header extraction 1 = Enable custom LG header extraction.

uint64_t cvmx_pki_pkind_parse::mpls_en

Enable MPLS parsing.

0 = Any MPLS labels are ignored, but may be handled by custom Ethertype PCAM matchers. 1 = MPLS label stacks are parsed and skipped over. PKI_GBL_PEN[MPLS_PEN] must be set.
